Class Item

  • java.lang.Object
    • Item
  • public class Item
extends java.lang.Object
    The class Item represents an item object with a length, width, height, weight, number of pages, type, and shape.

    • Constructor Summary

      Constructors 
      Constructor Description
      Item​(java.lang.String type, int length, int width)
      This constructor takes in the item's type, length, and width.
      Item​(java.lang.String type, int length, int width, int numPage)
      This is the constructor for document-type items.
      Item​(java.lang.String type, int length, int width, int height, double weight, boolean regularShape)
      This is the constructor for product-type and irregularly-sized items.

    • Method Detail

      • computeThickness

        public int computeThickness​(int numPage)
        This method is used to compute for the thickness of document-type item. 25 pages = 1 inch, round up on excess.
        Parameters:
        numPage - Indicates the number of pages of the document.
        Returns:
        The thickness of the document in inches.

      • computeWeight

        public int computeWeight​(int numPage)
        This method is used to compute for the weight of document-type item. 25 pages = 200g, round up on excess.
        Parameters:
        numPage - Indicates the number of pages of the document.
        Returns:
        The weight of the document in grams.
